Etymology: The new genus name is derived from the Greek Χίµαιρα (Latinized as
Chimaera
), a mythological creature composed of a lion, a goat and a snake, and from the Greek δασύς, shaggy, which refers to the dense facing with cilia of the ventral surface of Gastrotricha and which is often used as the second part of generic names of Macrodasyida .
